## ğŸ“Š **Git Reset Comparison Table**

| Command                    | Commit History (HEAD)    | Staging Area (Index)              | Working Directory (Files)            | Use Case ğŸ’¡                                     |
| -------------------------- | ------------------------ | --------------------------------- | ------------------------------------ | ----------------------------------------------- |
| `git reset --soft HEAD~1`  | âœ… Peeche chala jaata hai | âœ… Changes staged rehte hain       | âœ… Files as-it-is rehte hain          | Commit message change, commits ko combine karna |
| `git reset --mixed HEAD~1` | âœ… Peeche chala jaata hai | âŒ Staging area clear ho jaata hai | âœ… Files safe rehte hain (unstaged)   | Dobara modify karke commit karna                |
| `git reset --hard HEAD~1`  | âœ… Peeche chala jaata hai | âŒ Staging area clear              | âŒ Files bhi delete (purani state me) | Changes bilkul chhod dene hain                  |

